	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=17178&mid=107628013898520>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=17178&mid=107628013898520>Shamen</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=17178&mid=107628013898520#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sun, Feb 8th 10:42 PM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=280044><span id= >Belgereth the Wise</span></a><br><span id=notbold>16 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.33]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Just to make a point, and not to say other classes should not get this. In one sitting, I have to rebuff a group twice before an enchanter or cleric has to rebuff once. This is because shamen's stat buffs last 58 minutes. Focus of Soul and 7th last 1:25ish. There are a lot of spells we cast during grouping, here's a small list.&nbsp;&nbsp;Focus, Boar, Wrulan, Diaku, Replenishment, Talisman of Alacrity, Tribunal, Bih`li, Feral Avatar, (oddly Acumen), and rarely Levitate and EB. One cast of any small number of these is average all of your mana even with 305 wisdom.<br><br>Not saying shamen deserve it more, but I doubt we deserve it less.</p>&nbsp;<br>Belgereth Bloodstarr<br>65 Shaman of Rodcet Nife<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=203455" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=203455</a></td></tr>
